Although new norms pertaining to milk contamination have been introduced, are they the final solution to food safety issues? As evidenced by past experience in China, where the first food safety law was promulgated in 1965 and relevant legal frameworks were established in the 1990s, legislation alone seems not to completely eradicate unscrupulous food production in real practice. In the period from 1998 to 2007, thousands of people were sickened by food poisoning every year (Fig. 1
). Selected major food safety incidents reported in China over the past 5 years are listed in Table 1
